\subsection{Interface viewpoint}

SCALE exposes RESTful HTTP interfaces grouped by router prefix.

\begin{itemize}
    \item \texttt{/api/auth}: registration, login/logout, admin user management.
    \item \texttt{/api/challenges}: attack/fix/state/progress/hints for ten challenge tracks.
    \item \texttt{/api/project}, \texttt{/api/user/projects}: upload, scan, report, analytics.
    \item \texttt{/api/quizzes} and \texttt{/api/quiz}: static and dynamic quiz systems.
    \item \texttt{/api/stats}, \texttt{/api/instructor}: student/instructor/admin analytics.
    \item \texttt{/api/security}: log query and security statistics.
    \item \texttt{/api/messages}: threaded messaging and unread count.
    \item \texttt{/api/report/pdf}: student pentest PDF export.
\end{itemize}

\textbf{Representative interfaces}
\begin{itemize}
    \item \texttt{POST /api/auth/login}: credential verification, JWT issuance, role + approval enforcement.
    \item \texttt{POST /api/challenges/submit-fix}: sandbox validation and optional annotated code diff.
    \item \texttt{POST /api/project/scan}: static scan + risk scoring + persistence.
    \item \texttt{GET /api/stats/admin/dashboard}: aggregate operational metrics for admin panel.
\end{itemize}

\section{Data Design}

\subsection{Data Description}

The system uses relational persistence with SQLAlchemy models and MySQL storage.

\begin{itemize}
    \item Main transactional data: users, progress, scans, quizzes, logs, messaging.
    \item Challenge-specific data isolation: dedicated SQLi and CSRF lab databases.
    \item Timestamps are UTC (DateTime columns).
    \item Scan payloads are persisted as JSON-encoded text (\texttt{scan\_history.vuln\_summary}).
\end{itemize}

